Second— Uniserial. This consists of a creeping rooffing stem, termed sarmentum, which progresses by the succes- sive evolution of single fronds from its apex, each succeed- ing frond being produced from the base of the preceding one, at more or less distance in advance. It either con- tinues simple or brancheS‚ and varies in thickness from that of a thread to an inch or more in diameter, and is either epiqeous, hypoqeous‚ or epiphytal.
